article.headline: Lilly, Lesburt hit clutch 3s as Brown beats Harvard 71-68 in OT
article.description: — AJ Lesburt Jr. hit a 3-pointer with just under a minute left in overtime to give Brown the lead and Lyndel Erold and Kimo Ferrari both made two free throws to allow Brown to hold off Harvard 71-68.
article.linkText: Lilly, Lesburt hit clutch 3s as Brown beats Harvard 71-68 in OT

article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- — AJ Lesburt Jr. hit a 3-pointer with just under a minute left in overtime to give Brown the lead and Lyndel Erold and Kimo Ferrari both made two free throws to allow Brown to hold off Harvard 71-68. Kino Lilly Jr. hit a 3-pointer with five seconds left in regulation to pull the Bears even at 61-61 and force overtime. Lilly scored 16 points and added six rebounds and five assists for the Bears (10-17, 6-6 Ivy League). Nana Owusu-Anane scored 13 points and added 14 rebounds. Lesburt went 4 of 7 from the field to finish with 11 points. Malik Mack finished with 20 points, five assists and four steals for the Crimson (14-11, 5-7). Chisom Okpara added 15 points for Harvard. In addition, Louis Lesmond finished with 11 points and three steals. Both teams next play Saturday. Brown hosts Dartmouth and Harvard goes on the road to play Yale. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
